// Design AI Tools
// Higher-level scene graph manipulation: add, update, remove, group, align, duplicate, annotate,
// lint, export (SVG/code), and manage component instances — all operating on the serialized
// { rootId, nodes[] } scene graph without callers needing to construct raw JSON.

Scene graphs must follow: CANVAS root -> one or more PAGE children -> content nodes.
Node IDs are opaque generated strings. Unsafe structural fields (id, parentId, childIds, type) are
always stripped from caller-supplied property objects to prevent graph corruption.

---

FUNCTION getGraph(content) -> SerializedGraph                              EXPORT
  Validate that content has the expected { rootId, nodes[] } shape. Throw if not.

---

FUNCTION isTreeSpec(content) -> boolean                                    EXPORT
  Return true if content looks like a tree spec ({ type, ... }) rather than a scene graph.

---

FUNCTION treeToGraph(tree) -> SerializedGraph                              EXPORT
  Convert a recursive tree spec into a flat scene graph via buildNode.
  After building, call validateAndFixGraph to ensure CANVAS -> PAGE hierarchy.

---

FUNCTION buildNode(spec, parentId) -> nodeId
  Extract type, children, ref from spec. Apply convenience props. Create a default node.
  Attach to parent's childIds. Recurse into children.

---

FUNCTION getAbsolutePosition(graph, nodeId) -> { x, y }
  Walk up the parent chain summing x and y to get absolute canvas position.

---

FUNCTION findCurrentPage(graph) -> SerializedNode | null
  Return the first PAGE child of the CANVAS root, or null if none exists.

---

FUNCTION validateAndFixGraph(graph) -> SerializedGraph                     EXPORT
  If root is CANVAS: verify it has at least one PAGE child, return as-is.
  If root is PAGE: auto-wrap in a new CANVAS node.
  Any other root type: throw with a descriptive error.

---

FUNCTION createDefaultNode(type, overrides?) -> SerializedNode
  Return a new node with all fields initialized to safe defaults, merged with overrides.

---

FUNCTION hexToColor(hex) -> Color
  Parse a #RRGGBB or #RRGGBBAA hex string into normalized RGBA components (0-1 range).

---

FUNCTION solidFill(hex, opacity?) -> Fill
  Build a SOLID fill object from a hex color string and optional opacity.

---

FUNCTION solidStroke(hex, weight, opacity) -> Stroke
  Build a stroke descriptor from a hex color, weight, and opacity.

---

FUNCTION applyConvenienceProps(type, props) -> props
  Translate shorthand into scene graph form:
  - gap -> itemSpacing, align -> counterAxisAlign, justify -> primaryAxisAlign
  - fill (hex) -> fills array, stroke (hex) -> strokes array
  - padding (number) -> all four padding fields
  Auto-layout frames get HUG sizing defaults unless explicit sizes are given.
  TEXT gets width 200, height 24, textAutoResize HEIGHT, and a black fill by default.
  Strips all UNSAFE_PROPS before returning.

---

FUNCTION handleAddDesignNode(project, session, designId, args) -> { success, nodeId }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load the graph. Resolve target parent (from args or first page). Apply convenience props.
  Create a default node, attach to parent. Save and return the new node ID.

---

FUNCTION handleUpdateDesignNode(project, session, designId, nodeId, properties) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load the graph. Find the node. Translate convenience props in properties.
  Strip unsafe props, merge safe properties onto the node. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoveDesignNode(project, session, designId, nodeId) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load the graph. Collect the node and all descendants. Remove from parent's childIds.
  Delete all collected nodes from the graph. Save.

---

FUNCTION collectDescendants(id)
  Recursively add id and all child IDs to the idsToRemove set.

---

FUNCTION handleBatchDesignOperations(project, session, designId, operations) -> { success, results }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load the graph once. Maintain a temp-to-real ID map for cross-operation references.
  add: resolve parent, apply convenience props, create node, store real ID in idMap.
  update: resolve real ID, apply convenience props, merge safe props onto node.
  remove: resolve real ID, collect descendants, remove from parent, delete all.
  Save once at the end and return per-operation success results.

---

FUNCTION handleGetDesignNode(project, session, designId, nodeId) -> { success, node }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Load the graph. Find and return the node by ID. Throw if not found.

---

FUNCTION handleListDesignNodes(project, session, designId, parentId?, maxDepth?) -> { success, nodes }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Load the graph. Walk the subtree under parentId (or first page) up to maxDepth.
  Return a summary per node: id, name, type, x, y, width, height, depth, childCount.

---

FUNCTION walk(nodeId, depth)
  Recursively collect node summaries, stopping at maxDepth.

---

FUNCTION handleGroupDesignNodes(project, session, designId, nodeIds, name) -> { success, groupId }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Verify all nodes exist and share the same parent. Compute their bounding box.
  Create a GROUP node sized to the bounding box, inserted at the first selected node's position.
  Reparent all selected nodes into the group, adjusting positions to be relative to the group. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleUngroupDesignNodes(project, session, designId, nodeId) -> { success, childIds }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Find the GROUP. Reparent its children to the group's parent, restoring absolute positions.
  Replace the group in parent's childIds with the children. Delete the group node. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleReorderDesignNodes(project, session, designId, nodeIds, direction) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Group nodeIds by parent. For each parent, reorder childIds:
  front -> move to end, back -> move to start,
  forward -> step each node one position toward end,
  backward -> step each node one position toward start. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleDuplicateDesignNodes(project, session, designId, nodeIds, offsetX, offsetY) -> { success, newNodeIds }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Filter to top-level nodes (exclude nodes whose ancestors are already in the selection).
  For each, deep-clone the subtree with new IDs, offset root by offsetX/Y, append " copy" to name.
  Insert clone after the original in parent's childIds. Save.

---

FUNCTION cloneNode(srcId) -> newId
  Deep-clone a node and all its children with freshly generated IDs.

---

FUNCTION handleAlignDesignNodes(project, session, designId, nodeIds, action) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Compute absolute positions for all target nodes (handles cross-parent cases).
  left/right/top/bottom: align to the edge; centerH/centerV: align to bounding box center;
  distributeH/distributeV: evenly space between outermost nodes (requires 3+). Save.

---

FUNCTION setAbsX(n, absX) / setAbsY(n, absY)
  Adjust the node's local coordinate so its absolute position equals absX or absY.

---

FUNCTION handleTransformDesignNodes(project, session, designId, nodeIds, action) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Compute bounding box using absolute positions.
  flipH: mirror x across bounding box; flipV: mirror y across bounding box. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateDesignFromTree(project, session, designId, tree, parentId?) -> { success, nodeIds, rootNodeId }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load the graph. Recursively build nodes from the tree spec under the resolved parent.
  Collect ref->nodeId and name->nodeId mappings. Save and return.

---

FUNCTION buildNode(spec, pId) -> nodeId
  Apply convenience props, create default node, attach to parent. Record ref and name in nodeIds.

---

FUNCTION loadImageBytes(source, sourceType?) -> Buffer
  Auto-detect type (url/base64/file). Fetch, decode, or read the image. Return as Buffer.

---

FUNCTION addImageToGraph(graph, imageBytes) -> { imageHash, base64 }
  SHA-256 hash the bytes for a content-addressable key. Add to graph.images if not present.

---

FUNCTION handleAddDesignImage(project, session, designId, args) -> { success, nodeId, imageHash }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load image, add to image store. Create a FRAME with an IMAGE fill. Attach to parent. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleSetNodeImage(project, session, designId, nodeId, source, sourceType?, imageScaleMode?) -> { success, imageHash }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load image, add to image store. Replace or add an IMAGE fill on the target node. Save.

---

FUNCTION nodeToSVG(node, graph, defs) -> string
  Recursively render a scene node to an SVG element string.
  CANVAS/PAGE: traverse children silently. RECTANGLE/SECTION -> <rect>. ELLIPSE -> <ellipse>.
  TEXT -> <text> with font attributes. LINE -> <line>. GROUP -> children in translated <g>.
  FRAME -> background <rect> + optional clip path + children in translated <g>.
  IMAGE fills: register a <pattern> in defs.

---

FUNCTION escapeXml(str) -> string
  Escape XML special characters for safe embedding in SVG.

---

FUNCTION handleExportDesignSvg(project, session, designId, nodeId?, outputPath?) -> { success, svg, outputPath? }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Load graph. Render the root node's children via nodeToSVG, collecting defs.
  Wrap in an <svg> sized to the root. Optionally write to disk. Return SVG string.

---

FUNCTION buildStyleMap(node) -> StyleMap
  Build a CSS property map: dimensions, background, border, border-radius, rotation,
  flex layout, padding, overflow, flex-grow.

---

FUNCTION buildTextStyleMap(node, base) -> StyleMap
  Extend a base style map with text properties: font, text-align, color.

---

FUNCTION styleMapToReact(styles) -> string
  Serialize StyleMap as a React inline style object literal string.

---

FUNCTION styleMapToHTML(styles) -> string
  Serialize StyleMap as HTML inline style string (kebab-case, px units for lengths).

---

FUNCTION nodeToCode(node, graph, framework, indent) -> string
  Recursively render a scene node to HTML or React JSX.
  TEXT -> <span>; everything else -> <div> with inline styles. Recurse into children.

---

FUNCTION handleExportDesignCode(project, session, designId, nodeId?, framework, outputPath?) -> { success, code, outputPath? }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Load graph. Render children via nodeToCode.
  React: wrap in an exported function component named after the page.
  HTML: wrap in a full HTML document. Optionally write to disk. Return code string.

---

FUNCTION handleAnnotateNode(project, session, designId, nodeId, annotation) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Find the node. Merge-update its __annotations field (intent, notes, status, updatedAt). Save.

---

FUNCTION handleGetAnnotations(project, session, designId, statusFilter?) -> { success, annotations }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Collect all nodes with __annotations. Filter by status if provided. Return the list.

---

FUNCTION handleRemoveAnnotation(project, session, designId, nodeId) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Find the node. Delete its __annotations field. Save.

---

FUNCTION describeNode(nodeId, depth)
  Summary mode at depth > 2: count node types in stats without emitting lines.
  Otherwise: emit a text description line (type, name, position, size, key visual props).
  Detect zero-size and out-of-parent-bounds issues. Recurse into children.

---

FUNCTION handleDescribeDesign(project, session, designId, mode?) -> { success, description, issues, stats }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Load graph. Walk from first page via describeNode.
  Summary mode: only top 2 levels described; deeper nodes counted in stats only.
  Return text description, detected issues, and aggregate stats.

---

FUNCTION colorToHex(c) -> string
  Convert normalized Color to a #RRGGBB hex string.

---

FUNCTION relativeLuminance(c) -> number
  Compute WCAG relative luminance for a color.

---

FUNCTION contrastRatio(c1, c2) -> number
  Compute WCAG contrast ratio between two colors.

---

FUNCTION getAncestorFill(graph, nodeId) -> Color | null
  Walk up the parent chain to find the first ancestor with a visible solid fill.

---

FUNCTION handleLintDesign(project, session, designId) -> { success, issues }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Check every non-CANVAS, non-PAGE node for:
  - Orphaned parentId (error), zero size (error), entirely outside parent bounds (warning),
  - Text likely to overflow (warning), no visible fills on FRAME/RECTANGLE (warning),
  - Text contrast below 3.0:1 against nearest ancestor fill (warning),
  - Identical-position siblings (warning).

---

FUNCTION computeDesignDiff(currentGraph, previousGraph) -> DesignDiff       EXPORT
  Compare two graphs against a fixed DIFF_PROPERTIES list.
  New nodes -> added; missing nodes -> removed; property changes -> modified.
  Return { added, removed, modified, summary }.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateComponent(project, session, designId, nodeId) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Find the FRAME node. Change its type to COMPONENT. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateInstance(project, session, designId, componentId, parentId?, x?, y?) -> { success, instanceId }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Find the COMPONENT. Deep-clone it with new IDs. Set type to INSTANCE, link componentId,
  set position and name. Attach to resolved parent. Save.

---

FUNCTION cloneNode(srcId) -> newId
  Recursively deep-clone a node and its subtree with fresh IDs, adding all clones to graph.nodes.

---

FUNCTION handleListComponents(project, session, designId) -> { success, components }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Find all COMPONENT nodes and count their INSTANCE references. Return the list.

---

FUNCTION handleDetachInstance(project, session, designId, nodeId) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Find the INSTANCE node. Change type to FRAME, clear componentId. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleSaveComponent(project, session, designId, nodeId, componentName?) -> { success, path }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), saveComponentToLibrary (design-components)
  Find the COMPONENT. Collect the node and all descendants. Save subtree to the component library.

---

FUNCTION collectSubtree(id)
  Recursively collect node and all descendants into subtreeNodes.

---

FUNCTION handleLoadComponent(project, session, designId, componentName, parentId?, x?, y?) -> { success, nodeId }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design), loadComponentFromLibrary (design-components)
  Load the saved component subtree. Remap all IDs to fresh generated IDs.
  Attach root node to resolved parent with optional position. Add all nodes to graph. Save.

---

FUNCTION handleListLibraryComponents(project, session) -> { success, components }   EXPORT
  CALLS: listLibraryComponents (design-components)
  Delegate to the component library reader and return the component list.

---

FUNCTION handleDesignToDiagram(project, session, designId, maxDepth?, style?) -> { success, mermaidSource }   EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design)
  Load graph. Walk from root, emitting Mermaid nodes with classDefs per type.
  CANVAS and PAGE: traverse but do not emit. Component-map style: skip non-structural nodes.
  Connect parents to children with arrows. Return the Mermaid source string.

---

FUNCTION walkNode(nodeId, depth)
  Emit a Mermaid node definition. Recurse into children up to maxDepth.

---

FUNCTION sanitizeId(id) -> string
  Make a node ID safe for Mermaid (alphanumeric + underscore, no leading digit, non-empty).

---

FUNCTION escapeLabel(str) -> string
  Escape backslashes and double-quotes for safe embedding in a Mermaid label.

---

FUNCTION getClassForType(type) -> string
  Map a node type string to the corresponding Mermaid classDef name.
